Hello.
- Hello.

65
00:04:51,133 --> 00:04:53,378
[Happy music]

66
00:04:55,118 --> 00:04:57,921
[Happy music]

67
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:07,261
Toh Ti Ani Fuji

68
00:05:08,575 --> 00:05:11,016
Toh Ti Ani Fuji

69
00:05:17,187 --> 00:05:19,311
Come on. Shake your hands.

70
00:05:19,312 --> 00:05:21,353
Shake your hands.

71
00:05:21,354 --> 00:05:23,869
Come on, breathe.

72
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:24,721
[Laughing]

73
00:05:24,871 --> 00:05:26,646
A little ahead. Towards the edge.
- Okay.

74
00:05:27,159 --> 00:05:28,933
[Laughing loudly]

75
00:05:29,294 --> 00:05:31,228
Ma'am, you'll have to wait that side.
- No, please wait.

76
00:05:31,229 --> 00:05:31,770
Okay, okay. Sorry.

77
00:05:31,771 --> 00:05:34,891
No, waiting on the bridge is too risky. She'll have to go.
- Wait. Please wait.

78
00:05:34,977 --> 00:05:37,603
You've put on the
helmet. You are safe now.

79
00:05:37,604 --> 00:05:40,436
I told her about us.
- Whom?

80
00:05:40,594 --> 00:05:41,729
Kriti! I told Kriti.

81
00:05:41,973 --> 00:05:42,728
[Laughing

82
00:05:42,729 --> 00:05:44,846
I told her that things have
been happening between us.

83
00:05:44,847 --> 00:05:48,346
Why? Did I ask you
to tell her or leave her?

84
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,972
I wanted to try to
get serious about us.

85
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:54,180
But why are you
talking in the past tense?

86
00:05:54,438 --> 00:05:56,321
[Panting]

87
00:05:57,264 --> 00:05:59,688
When am I going to try it now?

88
00:05:59,689 --> 00:06:00,689
[Laughing]

89
00:06:01,248 --> 00:06:02,889
Come on, now. Let's get ready.

90
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,096
The only thing left is the jump.
There's no need to be scared.

91
00:06:06,097 --> 00:06:08,264
Step ahead. A little ahead.

92
00:06:09,361 --> 00:06:11,266
[Laughing]

93
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:13,007
Please don't forget me.

94
00:06:13,763 --> 00:06:15,799
[Crossing the heart]

95
00:06:16,850 --> 00:06:19,325
[Tense music]

96
00:06:25,423 --> 00:06:28,242
[Panting]

97
00:06:28,243 --> 00:06:29,715
[Breathing heavily]

98
00:06:32,317 --> 00:06:33,971
[Grins]

99
00:06:34,584 --> 00:06:35,591
[Smiles]

100
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:39,850
[Breathing heavily]

101
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,456
[Adventurous music]

102
00:06:55,266 --> 00:06:56,266
[Bangs]

103
00:06:56,449 --> 00:07:01,387
That's it? Only two
boys fell for you?

104
00:07:01,529 --> 00:07:02,596
[Laughing]

105
00:07:02,597 --> 00:07:06,353
Not enough to only like me. They
have to like my mother as well.

106
00:07:06,354 --> 00:07:08,065
We're a package deal, you see.

107
00:07:08,427 --> 00:07:10,173
[Laughing heartily]

108
00:07:10,174 --> 00:07:13,124
[Coughs]

109
00:07:15,554 --> 00:07:16,554
[Laughs]

110
00:07:17,055 --> 00:07:20,098
Are you looking at your
reflection in the spoon?

111
00:07:23,602 --> 00:07:24,602
[Grumps]

112
00:07:24,981 --> 00:07:26,138
[Chuckles]

113
00:07:26,139 --> 00:07:28,507
Did she feel giddy
again today? Hello?

114
00:07:29,338 --> 00:07:30,338
Did she feel?

115
00:07:32,054 --> 00:07:34,418
Okay, okay. Good.

116
00:07:34,758 --> 00:07:36,159
[Moving]

117
00:07:36,335 --> 00:07:38,951
Yes, the tremors are common.

118
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:46,594
Just put on the television for her.

119
00:07:48,055 --> 00:07:51,455
She won't really watch but
at least she won't bother you.

120
00:07:51,707 --> 00:07:53,119
Hello? Hello?

121
00:07:58,852 --> 00:08:00,472
[Footsteps]

122
00:08:02,257 --> 00:08:04,107
[Stands still]

123
00:08:04,885 --> 00:08:06,085
You do enough for your mother.

124
00:08:07,896 --> 00:08:08,896
What is enough?

125
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,640
There's no such thing as 'enough'.

126
00:08:14,016 --> 00:08:16,086
It's okay to choose
yourself once in a while.

127
00:08:16,547 --> 00:08:18,615
You need not feel like
such a criminal about it.

128
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:20,971
[Thuds]

129
00:08:20,972 --> 00:08:26,224
Will you please stop constantly staring
at your reflection? What a bore.

130
00:08:26,389 --> 00:08:27,389
[Chuckles]

131
00:08:28,714 --> 00:08:30,834
I'm not sure if Vismay
heard me clearly.

132
00:08:31,359 --> 00:08:32,531
[Stretching]

133
00:08:32,805 --> 00:08:33,954
He's sweet. The poor thing.

134
00:08:34,864 --> 00:08:36,504
Not as much of a
poor thing as you think.

135
00:08:36,812 --> 00:08:37,929
[Wind blowing]

136
00:08:38,279 --> 00:08:39,702
Why is that funny?

137
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,463
It's not going to be just one. I'm
planning to start a whole chain.

138
00:08:42,464 --> 00:08:46,554
So, you are going to start a whole chain of gyms.
- No. It's a body sculpting studio.

139
00:08:46,555 --> 00:08:48,237
That's the same as a gym!
- No!

140
00:08:48,238 --> 00:08:49,677
[Laughing]

141
00:08:50,305 --> 00:08:52,505
The focus will be on fitness
and the shape of the body.

142
00:08:52,863 --> 00:08:56,104
That is the same as a gym.
- No.

143
00:08:56,257 --> 00:08:57,527
[Laughs]

144
00:08:58,222 --> 00:08:59,043
Why don't you tell
me about your plan?

145
00:08:59,044 --> 00:09:00,044
[Water dripping]

146
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:03,805
I just want to give away
all my things and set off.

147
00:09:04,348 --> 00:09:06,341
[Water splashing]

148
00:09:10,261 --> 00:09:12,764
Where to?
- Anywhere.

149
00:09:13,107 --> 00:09:16,222
Never stop at any one
place. Just keep going.

150
00:09:16,491 --> 00:09:17,673
[Taps the metal]

151
00:09:18,264 --> 00:09:24,243
All my bags are packed, I'm ready to
go. I'm standin' here outside your door.

152
00:09:25,097 --> 00:09:31,513
Cause I'm leavin' on a jet plane,
Don't know when I'll be back again.

153
00:09:31,775 --> 00:09:32,870
[Humming]

154
00:09:33,959 --> 00:09:34,959
What happened?

155
00:09:38,612 --> 00:09:39,757
Hey, what's the matter?

156
00:09:41,055 --> 00:09:42,055
Let me see.

157
00:09:46,505 --> 00:09:47,505
What is it?

158
00:09:48,965 --> 00:09:50,213
[Tense music]

159
00:09:53,589 --> 00:09:54,589
Don't go.

160
00:09:55,722 --> 00:09:57,440
Where am I going?
- I mean ever.

161
00:10:00,472 --> 00:10:02,816
Don't ever go anywhere.
Just be with me. Always.

162
00:10:04,578 --> 00:10:05,936
[Chuckles]

163
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:08,430
I'm serious.

164
00:10:09,013 --> 00:10:10,679
[Tense music]

165
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:15,407
Never leave me. Promise?
- Okay.

166
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,151
No. Say it. Say you promise.

167
00:10:20,047 --> 00:10:21,637
I'm not going to?
- Say it.

168
00:10:22,239 --> 00:10:24,100
[Tense music]

169
00:10:24,597 --> 00:10:27,670
Okay. Promise.

170
00:10:28,272 --> 00:10:30,243
[Tense music]

171
00:10:41,465 --> 00:10:42,625
Still doing translations?

172
00:10:45,055 --> 00:10:47,055
I've been doing a lot of
subtitling work recently.

173
00:10:47,891 --> 00:10:49,873
Films and other things.

174
00:10:56,455 --> 00:11:00,287
So, are you in Tokyo on a holiday or...
- No, on work.

175
00:11:04,535 --> 00:11:05,535
The same thing?

176
00:11:05,947 --> 00:11:07,524
[Chuckles]

177
00:11:07,765 --> 00:11:09,637
[Both chuckle]

178
00:11:14,838 --> 00:11:16,009
[Footsteps]

179
00:11:16,222 --> 00:11:17,400
Wow. The plan changed?

180
00:11:19,255 --> 00:11:20,255
It just did.

181
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,100
[Grins]

182
00:11:23,180 --> 00:11:24,527
So, what do you do now?

183
00:11:26,005 --> 00:11:27,741
I do? things. I keep busy.

184
00:11:27,742 --> 00:11:30,962
[Other language]

185
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:33,971
Excuse me ma'am,
your table is ready.

186
00:11:33,972 --> 00:11:35,722
Thank you.

187
00:11:36,633 --> 00:11:38,560
[Indistinct chatter]

188
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:43,136
[Footsteps]

189
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,118
Cheers.
- Cheers.

190
00:11:45,589 --> 00:11:47,406
[Sipping tea]

191
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,333
[Thuds]

192
00:11:50,932 --> 00:11:52,169
Ma'am.
- Thank you so much.

193
00:11:52,749 --> 00:11:54,414
[Clutter]

194
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:59,592
The people here seem peaceful.
- A little too peaceful.

195
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,229
[Indistinct chatter]

196
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:06,162
You won't even catch them chatting on the train.
- No, I mean they seem content.

197
00:12:06,348 --> 00:12:06,917
[Indistinct chatter]

198
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:08,570
Do they?
- Hmm.

199
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:13,146
Actually, if they had toilet seats like
these everywhere, anyone would seem content.

200
00:12:13,147 --> 00:12:14,921
[Chuckling]

201
00:12:15,797 --> 00:12:16,797
[Chuckle]

202
00:12:17,417 --> 00:12:18,709
[Giggling]

203
00:12:19,547 --> 00:12:23,778
I sat on the commode in my hotel?
Such a wonderfully warm seat.

204
00:12:24,214 --> 00:12:28,246
And so many options for washing your
bum! I've never been more grateful.

205
00:12:29,319 --> 00:12:31,125
[Laughing]

206
00:12:32,422 --> 00:12:34,092
How are you still single?

207
00:12:34,957 --> 00:12:35,997
[Clutter]

208
00:12:37,103 --> 00:12:38,538
[Indistinct chatter]

209
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:41,165
[Indistinct chatter]

210
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:44,034
Who said I am?
- You're not?

211
00:12:44,713 --> 00:12:45,713
I am.

212
00:12:46,278 --> 00:12:47,278
[Indistinct chatter]

213
00:12:47,997 --> 00:12:48,605
And you?

214
00:12:48,606 --> 00:12:49,870
[Tense music]

215
00:12:50,724 --> 00:12:52,552
[Chuckling]

216
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:56,143
[Pensive music]

217
00:12:56,722 --> 00:12:58,679
Enough. I'm done.
- Have more, come on.

218
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:01,662
It's sake. You won't feel cold.
Come on. Down it.

219
00:13:01,663 --> 00:13:03,392
Drink it!

220
00:13:03,847 --> 00:13:05,430
Cheers.
- Cheers.

221
00:13:06,044 --> 00:13:07,845
[Laughing]

222
00:13:07,846 --> 00:13:09,608
Hmm.

223
00:13:09,609 --> 00:13:11,037
[Sighs]

224
00:13:12,362 --> 00:13:15,444
By the way, what's with the policy
of not talking about your work?

225
00:13:15,445 --> 00:13:17,054
[Chuckles]

226
00:13:17,055 --> 00:13:17,677
What?

227
00:13:17,678 --> 00:13:18,263
[Chuckles]

228
00:13:18,535 --> 00:13:19,374
There's no policy.

229
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:20,375
Then?

230
00:13:21,555 --> 00:13:22,555
I don't want to tell you.

231
00:13:23,081 --> 00:13:23,584
Why?

232
00:13:23,847 --> 00:13:26,573
Because you always judge.

233
00:13:27,089 --> 00:13:29,978
Wait, hold on. 'Always'?
When was the last time we met?

234
00:13:30,395 --> 00:13:32,749
Yes, okay, sorry. You used to.

235
00:13:33,077 --> 00:13:36,734
But a person's true nature
never changes, right?

236
00:13:37,194 --> 00:13:39,044
[Sighs]

237
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,639
[Indistinct laughter]

238
00:13:41,922 --> 00:13:45,482
What?
- Your mind is made up. Leave it.

239
00:13:45,646 --> 00:13:46,429
[Indistinct chatter]

240
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:52,117
Oh no. Okay, fine. I'll tell you.
- No, no, no? I don't even want to know.

241
00:13:52,464 --> 00:13:55,139
Why wouldn't I want to share it with you?
- Who knows?

242
00:13:55,339 --> 00:13:57,170
Come on.
- No, no, no, no. I don't want to know anymore.

243
00:13:57,171 --> 00:13:59,979
Now, I want to tell you. Listen to me!
- No, no, no!

244
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:01,971
[Laughing]

245
00:14:02,332 --> 00:14:04,599
[Laughing loudly]

246
00:14:04,873 --> 00:14:07,106
[Soft music]

247
00:14:07,697 --> 00:14:09,876
[Soft music continues]

248
00:14:27,404 --> 00:14:30,656
[Harmonious music]

249
00:15:02,992 --> 00:15:05,247
[Harmonious music]

250
00:15:13,076 --> 00:15:18,068
[Harmonious music]

251
00:15:21,517 --> 00:15:24,232
[Train chugging]

252
00:15:31,229 --> 00:15:34,853
[Train chugging speedily]

253
00:15:42,988 --> 00:15:46,382
[Footsteps]

254
00:15:50,225 --> 00:15:53,138
[Train bell]

255
00:15:54,528 --> 00:15:58,481
[Tense music]

256
00:16:06,024 --> 00:16:09,353
[Tense music]

257
00:16:09,692 --> 00:16:11,587
[Ambulance siren]

258
00:16:11,871 --> 00:16:14,816
[Tense music]

259
00:16:14,992 --> 00:16:17,170
[Tense music]

260
00:16:17,576 --> 00:16:19,021
[Train speeding]

261
00:16:21,134 --> 00:16:23,214
[Footsteps]

262
00:16:23,871 --> 00:16:26,718
[Heavy strides]

263
00:16:29,718 --> 00:16:32,433
[Indistinct chatter]

264
00:16:34,503 --> 00:16:37,152
Hello? I'm glad you called.

265
00:16:37,393 --> 00:16:38,393
[Footsteps]

266
00:16:38,555 --> 00:16:41,740
I'm sorry. I got carried away?

267
00:16:41,915 --> 00:16:43,382
[Train chugging]

268
00:16:44,055 --> 00:16:45,055
Right now?

269
00:16:45,583 --> 00:16:46,765
[Footsteps]

270
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:48,835
Sure, okay.
I'll be right there.

271
00:16:49,338 --> 00:16:50,981
[Footsteps]

272
00:16:56,970 --> 00:16:59,400
[Long strides]

273
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:01,842
[Knocking]

274
00:17:11,127 --> 00:17:13,623
[Tense music]

275
00:17:15,944 --> 00:17:17,466
[Footsteps]

276
00:17:20,499 --> 00:17:21,499
[Chimes]

277
00:17:28,229 --> 00:17:29,948
[Door shuts]

278
00:17:33,944 --> 00:17:35,357
[Footsteps]

279
00:17:39,473 --> 00:17:40,473
[Door opens]

280
00:18:06,966 --> 00:18:09,375
[Tense music]

281
00:18:12,035 --> 00:18:14,061
[Footsteps]

282
00:18:16,371 --> 00:18:17,970
[Door closes]

283
00:18:21,386 --> 00:18:23,159
[Tense music]

284
00:18:23,554 --> 00:18:25,459
[Stops]

285
00:18:27,462 --> 00:18:30,112
[Sighs]

286
00:18:30,769 --> 00:18:32,685
[Sighs]

287
00:18:42,364 --> 00:18:44,608
[Wipes eyes]

288
00:18:46,732 --> 00:18:49,360
[Tense music]

289
00:19:00,211 --> 00:19:02,116
[Suspenseful music]

290
00:19:03,639 --> 00:19:05,127
Hello!

291
00:19:06,046 --> 00:19:07,295
Hi!

292
00:19:08,222 --> 00:19:09,472
Where are you?

293
00:19:09,714 --> 00:19:10,714
[Squealing]

294
00:19:10,889 --> 00:19:13,764
Who is it? Who is he talking to?

295
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:15,900
[Distorted voice

296
00:19:18,419 --> 00:19:20,904
We're not missing you! He's lying!

297
00:19:21,123 --> 00:19:26,639
Are you at home? Are you at home?
Are you at home? Are you at home?

298
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:28,375
Yes.

299
00:19:28,995 --> 00:19:30,073
[Loud music]

300
00:19:30,074 --> 00:19:31,678
[Loud music playing]

301
00:19:31,930 --> 00:19:34,180
Hold, hold, hold.

302
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:41,335
What did you want?

303
00:19:42,594 --> 00:19:46,347
I want you? here? now.

304
00:19:46,623 --> 00:19:47,623
Hello!

305
00:19:47,805 --> 00:19:50,904
Right now. Right here.

306
00:19:51,442 --> 00:19:52,942
[Muffled voice]

307
00:19:53,292 --> 00:19:54,923
[Beeps]

308
00:20:00,485 --> 00:20:01,756
[Dialing tone]

309
00:20:07,274 --> 00:20:08,993
[Groans]

310
00:20:09,507 --> 00:20:10,843
[Voice on phone]

311
00:20:12,354 --> 00:20:14,763
[Grunts]

312
00:20:25,649 --> 00:20:27,428
[Clutters]

313
00:20:27,429 --> 00:20:29,498
[Grunts]

314
00:20:29,499 --> 00:20:31,901
[Voice on phone]

315
00:20:32,273 --> 00:20:35,197
[Breathing heavily]

316
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:37,430
[Grunts]

317
00:20:37,704 --> 00:20:39,927
[Monitor beeps]

318
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:43,759
[Groans]

319
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:47,011
[Groans]

320
00:20:47,186 --> 00:20:49,638
[Breathing heavily]

321
00:21:03,355 --> 00:21:05,763
[Shivering]

322
00:21:22,318 --> 00:21:23,318
[Exhales]

323
00:21:24,584 --> 00:21:25,584
[Sighs]

324
00:21:32,687 --> 00:21:34,844
[Clangs]

325
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:38,019
[Whirring]

326
00:21:39,661 --> 00:21:41,282
[Clangs]

327
00:21:41,807 --> 00:21:44,621
[Chugging]

328
00:21:45,453 --> 00:21:47,271
[Clangs]

329
00:21:48,814 --> 00:21:49,814
[Clangs]

330
00:21:52,662 --> 00:21:55,163
[Clangs]

331
00:21:55,164 --> 00:21:57,326
[Whirring]

332
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,216
[Crow caws]

333
00:22:12,643 --> 00:22:15,348
[Soft cry]

334
00:22:23,351 --> 00:22:24,797
[Bee buzzing]

335
00:22:25,014 --> 00:22:29,034
When my uncle died, my cousin stopped
being able to listen to music.

336
00:22:29,672 --> 00:22:32,921
Hmm. The universe
always maintains its balance.

337
00:22:33,639 --> 00:22:36,260
Yes, when something is destroyed,
something else is created.

338
00:22:36,742 --> 00:22:40,169
My uncle died in the Kedarnath
floods. We didn't even get to see him.

339
00:22:40,881 --> 00:22:41,881
[Clangs]

340
00:22:42,326 --> 00:22:45,006
At least you got to say a final
goodbye. At least you were prepared.

341
00:22:45,297 --> 00:22:51,917
Lavender perfume reduces stress. Especially when
you're sad. Especially when you've experienced loss.

342
00:22:52,464 --> 00:22:57,402
Balance. It's about balance in the universe.
- When one leaves, another arrives.

343
00:22:57,545 --> 00:22:58,968
[Sprang up]

344
00:22:59,286 --> 00:23:00,906
[Heavy footsteps]

345
00:23:02,209 --> 00:23:04,404
[Footsteps]

346
00:23:04,405 --> 00:23:05,954
[Door shuts]

347
00:23:07,092 --> 00:23:08,253
[Knocks]

348
00:23:09,906 --> 00:23:11,318
[Knocking loudly]

349
00:23:12,586 --> 00:23:13,586
What's wrong?

350
00:23:15,139 --> 00:23:18,396
We're sorry if one of
us said the wrong thing.

351
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,797
Listen? just come out. Let's talk.

352
00:23:21,208 --> 00:23:24,227
You should be with people right now. Why
have you locked yourself in there alone?

353
00:23:24,228 --> 00:23:25,355
[Knocking]

354
00:23:25,580 --> 00:23:28,078
At least say something.
I'm getting worried.

355
00:23:28,357 --> 00:23:29,357
I'm pregnant.

356
00:23:32,814 --> 00:23:34,155
[Chuckles]

357
00:23:35,113 --> 00:23:36,113
[Garbles water]

358
00:23:36,468 --> 00:23:37,946
I said I'm pregnant.

359
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:41,272
[Sips water]

360
00:23:44,172 --> 00:23:45,638
Aren't you going to say anything?

361
00:23:47,061 --> 00:23:48,566
[Clears throat]

362
00:23:49,278 --> 00:23:53,220
Yes, of course I do.

363
00:23:54,602 --> 00:23:55,724
[Mummbles]

364
00:24:00,378 --> 00:24:02,307
[Unlatches door]

365
00:24:02,978 --> 00:24:04,916
[Running]

366
00:24:04,917 --> 00:24:08,617
[Footsteps]

367
00:24:09,629 --> 00:24:12,339
[Footsteps]

368
00:24:12,955 --> 00:24:14,173
Wait.

369
00:24:24,616 --> 00:24:25,820
This way, Ma'am.

370
00:24:27,705 --> 00:24:29,077
Please.
- Thanks.

371
00:24:31,464 --> 00:24:32,464
Thank you.
- Thank you.

372
00:24:32,786 --> 00:24:35,469
[Soft music]

373
00:24:36,085 --> 00:24:38,480
[Indistinct chatter]

374
00:24:39,465 --> 00:24:40,465
[Clangs]

375
00:24:45,063 --> 00:24:47,170
[Soft music]

376
00:24:54,269 --> 00:24:56,486
[Clangs]

377
00:24:57,349 --> 00:24:58,349
Thank you.

378
00:25:11,185 --> 00:25:13,279
Ma'am, sake.
- Thank you.

379
00:25:14,338 --> 00:25:15,338
Cheers

380
00:25:16,580 --> 00:25:17,580
Yes, Sir?

381
00:25:23,147 --> 00:25:24,147
[Shifts chair]

382
00:25:24,570 --> 00:25:25,570
[Pulls chair]

383
00:25:32,974 --> 00:25:33,974
[Lifts glass]

384
00:25:42,718 --> 00:25:44,046
[Thuds]

385
00:25:47,591 --> 00:25:48,959
Are we going to talk?

386
00:25:50,255 --> 00:25:51,258
Wait, let me order first.

387
00:25:52,071 --> 00:25:53,071
Yes, sir?

388
00:25:54,981 --> 00:25:55,981
Uh!

389
00:25:57,117 --> 00:25:58,117
Salmon?

390
00:25:59,211 --> 00:26:02,532
And? Tuna Sashimi
- Thank you, Sir.

391
00:26:03,011 --> 00:26:05,146
[Soft music]

392
00:26:08,348 --> 00:26:10,429
Can you take off your sunglasses at least?
- Why?

393
00:26:15,588 --> 00:26:17,504
[Shifts chair]

394
00:26:17,860 --> 00:26:19,776
[Footsteps]

395
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:25,894
[Indistinct chatter]

396
00:26:26,332 --> 00:26:28,905
[Children giggling]

397
00:26:31,081 --> 00:26:33,818
[Door opens]

398
00:26:37,883 --> 00:26:38,883
[Clangs]

399
00:26:43,891 --> 00:26:45,451
[Pouring water]

400
00:26:46,026 --> 00:26:47,026
[Clang]

401
00:26:47,641 --> 00:26:49,968
[Clangs]

402
00:26:50,187 --> 00:26:51,295
[Spray]

403
00:26:52,650 --> 00:26:55,757
[Clang]

404
00:26:58,289 --> 00:27:00,246
[Scraping]

405
00:27:00,456 --> 00:27:03,531
Kartu, why aren't
you saying anything?

406
00:27:04,580 --> 00:27:05,680
I'm watching.

407
00:27:09,694 --> 00:27:10,974
Why don't you show him our home?

408
00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:13,111
What's there to show?

409
00:27:19,130 --> 00:27:21,450
Don't you understand? I'm
asking you to show him the house.

410
00:27:22,951 --> 00:27:23,951
You can start.

411
00:27:29,055 --> 00:27:30,287
Tell him your friends' names.

412
00:27:30,999 --> 00:27:31,999
Hmm.

413
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:36,952
Tomoki, Ayano, Riko, Kiho.

414
00:27:37,472 --> 00:27:39,936
And what's her
name? Your girlfriend?

415
00:27:40,414 --> 00:27:41,414
Masako.

416
00:27:42,071 --> 00:27:43,071
[Chuckles]

417
00:27:44,389 --> 00:27:47,272
Aren't you going to eat?
- No, I'm a pescatarian.

418
00:27:48,889 --> 00:27:52,103
What's that?
- I only eat fish.

419
00:27:54,484 --> 00:27:55,484
It's just a phase.

420
00:27:56,797 --> 00:27:57,797
[Clang]

421
00:27:59,630 --> 00:28:02,135
[Clang]

422
00:28:02,290 --> 00:28:07,883
Are you an old friend of Ma's?
- Yes, I am.

423
00:28:08,705 --> 00:28:11,660
From school?
- No.

424
00:28:12,536 --> 00:28:14,480
So, not that old.

425
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:17,491
[Shakes head]

426
00:28:18,777 --> 00:28:20,852
[Clang]

427
00:28:20,853 --> 00:28:23,978
I should get going. I have got a meeting.
- Oh...

428
00:28:24,222 --> 00:28:25,743
Don't you want to see the house?

429
00:28:26,263 --> 00:28:28,576
[Exhales]

430
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:31,122
Sure.
- Let's go then.

431
00:28:31,492 --> 00:28:34,100
[Picks toy car]

432
00:28:34,101 --> 00:28:36,008
[Footsteps]

433
00:28:36,939 --> 00:28:39,991
[Sighs]

434
00:28:44,083 --> 00:28:45,944
[Footsteps]

435
00:28:47,532 --> 00:28:49,106
[Footsteps]

436
00:28:49,863 --> 00:28:53,034
His name is 'Table'.
This is where I study.

437
00:28:55,237 --> 00:29:00,430
His name is 'Bed'. This
is where I sleep and read.

438
00:29:01,081 --> 00:29:06,241
His name is 'Rug'. This
is where I draw and read.

439
00:29:08,266 --> 00:29:10,278
His name is 'Cat'.

440
00:29:12,505 --> 00:29:13,905
Her name is 'Window'.

441
00:29:17,755 --> 00:29:20,570
Nice. You have a lovely room.

442
00:29:25,251 --> 00:29:26,251
Wow.

443
00:29:29,466 --> 00:29:31,108
Isn't this Mount Fuji?

444
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,147
Yes. Fuji is my friend.

445
00:29:35,378 --> 00:29:39,115
This mountain?
- Yes. Fuji and I are very close.

446
00:29:39,785 --> 00:29:43,754
Did you make this drawing?
- Yes. It took me three whole days.

447
00:29:44,174 --> 00:29:50,073
Kartu, you liar! It was already on
the wall when we moved in here.

448
00:29:52,158 --> 00:29:53,677
Your friend is wonderful, Kartu.

449
00:29:54,306 --> 00:29:55,387
Hold on.

450
00:29:55,388 --> 00:29:58,507
Only my Ma and my
Pa are allowed to call me

451
00:29:58,508 --> 00:30:01,286
'Kartu'.
And Nori-ba chan. And Haru-ji chan.

452
00:30:01,519 --> 00:30:05,310
And my friend Tomoki. And
my friend Fuji-san, of course.

453
00:30:06,035 --> 00:30:09,717
I'm sorry, Kartikeya. I'll keep in mind.
- It's okay.

454
00:30:15,013 --> 00:30:19,051
Are these your friends too?
- No! That's my Ma and Pa.

455
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:21,925
They are very old
friends. From school.

456
00:30:23,923 --> 00:30:25,086
His name is Vismay.

457
00:30:30,205 --> 00:30:34,407
[Tense music]

458
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,932
It's not all that shocking.

459
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:48,859
We grew up next door to each other.
No one knows me like he does.

460
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:52,459
So, you married him. Wow.

461
00:30:57,646 --> 00:31:00,173
I was completely alone
after you cut me off.

462
00:31:04,010 --> 00:31:05,912
I had no one else in Pune.

463
00:31:06,501 --> 00:31:10,757
I was alone. So, I made the
decision to shift here with him.

464
00:31:15,055 --> 00:31:16,108
What?
- Nothing.

465
00:31:17,203 --> 00:31:18,873
Say it.
- It's nothing.

466
00:31:19,817 --> 00:31:22,098
I'm happy to see that you got
everything you ever wanted.

467
00:31:24,655 --> 00:31:26,510
I got none of what I wanted.

468
00:31:29,364 --> 00:31:31,286
Here, take this.

469
00:31:32,135 --> 00:31:34,304
Aren't you coming home?
- No.

470
00:31:34,995 --> 00:31:38,170
Why not?
- You've given me enough to digest.

471
00:31:39,229 --> 00:31:40,990
That's not fair.
- Sure, that's not fair.

472
00:31:43,631 --> 00:31:47,340
Congratulations. Whatever. Bye.

473
00:31:50,159 --> 00:31:53,595
[Tense music]

474
00:32:00,711 --> 00:32:04,051
[Sighs]

475
00:32:06,364 --> 00:32:08,430
[Tense music]

476
00:32:13,138 --> 00:32:14,411
[Clangs]

477
00:32:14,863 --> 00:32:18,544
[Clangs]

478
00:32:18,996 --> 00:32:21,651
[Motor whirring]

479
00:32:22,349 --> 00:32:24,512
[Straps]

480
00:32:25,757 --> 00:32:27,126
[Thuds]

481
00:32:29,261 --> 00:32:30,629
Her cupboard is emptied.

482
00:32:31,697 --> 00:32:34,763
[Footsteps]

483
00:32:35,857 --> 00:32:37,500
[Whirring]

484
00:32:43,234 --> 00:32:46,368
We don't have to do this all today.
We can do it later.

485
00:32:47,819 --> 00:32:50,406
[Tense music]

486
00:32:50,652 --> 00:32:52,486
No. Today is fine.

487
00:32:53,307 --> 00:32:57,112
[Clangs]

488
00:32:59,130 --> 00:33:00,838
You have been looking after
your mother for all these years.

489
00:33:00,839 --> 00:33:04,174
Do you even know any other kind of
life? Weren't you a mother to her?

490
00:33:05,255 --> 00:33:06,870
I can imagine myself as a mother.

491
00:33:07,103 --> 00:33:09,423
Are you immediately going to
take on a new responsibility?

492
00:33:09,580 --> 00:33:12,460
But then I'm being selfish, right?
- Yes. And why not? Please be selfish.

493
00:33:12,919 --> 00:33:15,041
So, we're both saying we
don't want this right now?

494
00:33:16,380 --> 00:33:17,655
I'm saying?

495
00:33:18,435 --> 00:33:20,179
[Vehicle speeding]

496
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:21,501
We'll do whatever you want.

497
00:33:22,405 --> 00:33:26,688
She cannot always be the one to make the difficult decision.
- I'm trying to be sensitive.

498
00:33:26,925 --> 00:33:27,495
Okay.

499
00:33:27,728 --> 00:33:29,022
[Car speeding]

500
00:33:29,023 --> 00:33:29,871
Okay.

501
00:33:29,872 --> 00:33:31,609
[Car honking]

502
00:33:31,610 --> 00:33:32,614
[Thuds]

503
00:33:38,677 --> 00:33:40,880
[Clinking]

504
00:33:41,879 --> 00:33:43,960
[Tearing]

505
00:33:49,763 --> 00:33:51,665
[Clang]

506
00:33:52,226 --> 00:33:54,252
[Door opens]

507
00:33:54,580 --> 00:33:56,565
Hello. How are you?
- Good.

508
00:33:57,530 --> 00:33:59,342
Are you sure you want to go ahead with it?
- Yes.

509
00:33:59,343 --> 00:34:03,093
Okay, then. Lie down. I'll explain the procedure to you.
- Okay.

510
00:34:03,722 --> 00:34:07,828
We will first put your legs in the
stirrups, then anaesthetize your cervix.

511
00:34:08,307 --> 00:34:12,523
It is called a para-cervical block.
After that, we will use a rod...

512
00:34:12,687 --> 00:34:14,222
Here?
- Yes, please. Lie down.

513
00:34:15,438 --> 00:34:21,788
A rod will be inserted and then we will
clear everything using a suction tube.

514
00:34:22,289 --> 00:34:24,025
It's a short ten minute procedure.

515
00:34:24,586 --> 00:34:27,104
Let me know if you feel
uneasy. And don't be afraid.

516
00:34:28,922 --> 00:34:30,895
Is the block done?
- Yes, ma'am.

517
00:34:31,171 --> 00:34:32,991
[Indistinct chatter]

518
00:34:33,664 --> 00:34:35,290
Okay. Get the instruments ready.

519
00:34:38,643 --> 00:34:42,038
[Indistinct chatter]

520
00:34:43,264 --> 00:34:46,102
Drum. And the cap and mask.
- Yes, ma'am.

521
00:34:46,430 --> 00:34:47,670
Okay, let's start.

522
00:34:47,671 --> 00:34:49,360
[Tense music]

523
00:34:49,784 --> 00:34:56,203
[Sweeping]

524
00:34:57,996 --> 00:35:00,897
[Sighs]

525
00:35:07,535 --> 00:35:09,150
[Grunts]

526
00:35:12,343 --> 00:35:14,364
I can't imagine what
is going to happen.

527
00:35:16,006 --> 00:35:19,798
She is allowed to be confused.

528
00:35:20,797 --> 00:35:23,027
She should tell him.

529
00:35:23,944 --> 00:35:27,188
[Birds chirping]

530
00:35:28,269 --> 00:35:30,267
[Footsteps]

531
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:33,689
[Pouring liquid]

532
00:35:43,721 --> 00:35:49,004
He is his son. He
has the right to know.

533
00:35:49,264 --> 00:35:50,550
[Inhaling]

534
00:35:50,733 --> 00:35:52,165
I'm confused.

535
00:35:53,506 --> 00:35:54,506
Are you really?

536
00:35:55,477 --> 00:35:58,517
Or are you going to ask for advice and
then as always do exactly as you wish?

537
00:35:58,614 --> 00:35:59,614
Is that what I do?

538
00:35:59,930 --> 00:36:02,676
You said you didn't know where
to go. I said let's shift to Japan.

539
00:36:03,278 --> 00:36:07,398
You asked if we should get married. I said
okay, but I wanted to work on our relationship.

540
00:36:08,372 --> 00:36:11,972
Then you said we should get married but let's
not get involved and keep each other trapped.

541
00:36:12,430 --> 00:36:14,630
Yes, but I...
- When I asked you why get married at all.

542
00:36:14,822 --> 00:36:16,048
You said, “For Kartu's sake.”

543
00:36:16,514 --> 00:36:18,634
If you didn't want this,
you shouldn't have agreed.

544
00:36:19,473 --> 00:36:23,389
I was alone. I was afraid. So, in the moment,
I did what I thought was right for Kartikeya.

545
00:36:24,504 --> 00:36:27,803
I had made it absolutely clear to you that
I felt nothing for you but friendship.

546
