1386
01:21:07,413 --> 01:21:08,665
[Sobs]

1387
01:21:09,497 --> 01:21:11,670
[Muffled sobs]

1388
01:21:12,405 --> 01:21:13,886
[Sighs]

1389
01:21:14,867 --> 01:21:16,268
[Tense music]

1390
01:21:18,239 --> 01:21:20,508
[Sniffs]

1391
01:21:20,840 --> 01:21:22,960
[Sighs]

1392
01:21:24,870 --> 01:21:25,870
Yes, Vismay?

1393
01:21:26,980 --> 01:21:28,969
[Tense music]

1394
01:21:30,108 --> 01:21:31,108
[Intense music]

1395
01:21:31,964 --> 01:21:34,437
We have to take care of
this plaster for six weeks.

1396
01:21:34,872 --> 01:21:38,551
Make sure it doesn't get wet.

1397
01:21:40,049 --> 01:21:42,524
[Ambulance siren]

1398
01:21:42,525 --> 01:21:44,096
[Footsteps]

1399
01:21:47,284 --> 01:21:48,931
[Sighs]

1400
01:21:52,097 --> 01:21:53,362
His arm is fractured.

1401
01:21:53,363 --> 01:21:56,563
But the doctor has said there's nothing
to worry about. It should be better soon.

1402
01:21:57,294 --> 01:21:57,811
Well.

1403
01:21:58,170 --> 01:21:59,810
The bank manager
was being uncooperative.

1404
01:22:00,228 --> 01:22:02,566
So, he lost his temper and smashed
his glass table with his own hand.

1405
01:22:02,567 --> 01:22:05,484
Please don't say anything to him
right now. We'll talk to him later.

1406
01:22:05,869 --> 01:22:09,487
What sense does it make, if in a fit of
rage, you end up causing harm to yourself?

1407
01:22:10,695 --> 01:22:11,695
[Cutting]

1408
01:22:12,596 --> 01:22:13,726
[Clang]

1409
01:22:14,839 --> 01:22:15,977
[Tearing]

1410
01:22:16,441 --> 01:22:17,720
[Tearing]

1411
01:22:19,034 --> 01:22:20,034
[Tearing]

1412
01:22:20,278 --> 01:22:22,301
[Tearing]

1413
01:22:22,976 --> 01:22:24,640
[Tearing]

1414
01:22:28,748 --> 01:22:30,648
[Wrapping]

1415
01:22:31,069 --> 01:22:33,767
[Pouring water]

1416
01:22:34,397 --> 01:22:37,191
[Sniffs]

1417
01:22:37,498 --> 01:22:39,004
[Tense music]

1418
01:22:39,828 --> 01:22:41,632
[Sobs]

1419
01:22:42,315 --> 01:22:44,321
[Soft music]

1420
01:22:47,073 --> 01:22:49,735
[Sobs]

1421
01:22:51,303 --> 01:22:53,510
[Sighs]

1422
01:22:55,385 --> 01:22:57,373
[Tense music]

1423
01:22:58,652 --> 01:23:01,008
[Sighs]

1424
01:23:01,175 --> 01:23:02,716
[Sighs]

1425
01:23:03,163 --> 01:23:04,705
[Tense music]

1426
01:23:07,884 --> 01:23:10,232
[Tense music]

1427
01:23:10,398 --> 01:23:12,054
[Tense music]

1428
01:23:12,404 --> 01:23:14,804
[Tense music]

1429
01:23:15,715 --> 01:23:18,124
[Water splashing]

1430
01:23:18,824 --> 01:23:19,972
[Tense music]

1431
01:23:21,277 --> 01:23:22,477
[Tense music]

1432
01:23:24,054 --> 01:23:25,451
Kartu?

1433
01:23:25,452 --> 01:23:26,953
[Tense music]

1434
01:23:27,767 --> 01:23:28,871
[Tense music]

1435
01:23:29,861 --> 01:23:31,411
[Tense music]

1436
01:23:32,068 --> 01:23:33,986
[Water splashing]

1437
01:23:42,351 --> 01:23:43,613
[Clangs]

1438
01:23:43,832 --> 01:23:45,294
[Clangs]

1439
01:23:53,090 --> 01:23:54,166
Hey, champ.

1440
01:23:54,167 --> 01:23:55,455
[Grins]

1441
01:23:55,910 --> 01:23:56,905
[Kissing hand]

1442
01:23:56,906 --> 01:23:57,906
[Kissing]

1443
01:24:00,069 --> 01:24:01,129
[Hugging]

1444
01:24:02,944 --> 01:24:05,526
If you had to leave so soon, why
did you even bother coming back?

1445
01:24:06,805 --> 01:24:08,110
[Nods]

1446
01:24:08,714 --> 01:24:10,518
[Holding tight]

1447
01:24:19,129 --> 01:24:20,740
[Footsteps]

1448
01:24:22,939 --> 01:24:23,939
[Door closes]

1449
01:24:24,568 --> 01:24:25,568
[Clangs]

1450
01:24:27,073 --> 01:24:28,282
[Sits]

1451
01:24:28,948 --> 01:24:30,121
Vismay?
- Not okay.

1452
01:24:34,422 --> 01:24:36,384
Once you let him into Kartu's life,

1453
01:24:37,129 --> 01:24:39,678
every decision from that point
on, will have to be Kartu's own.

1454
01:24:40,685 --> 01:24:42,235
[Sighs]

1455
01:24:43,759 --> 01:24:44,942
[Rustles]

1456
01:24:52,308 --> 01:24:53,815
I've known Kartu since he was born.

1457
01:24:54,104 --> 01:24:55,427
[Intense stare]

1458
01:24:55,812 --> 01:24:57,424
I've brought him up along with you.

1459
01:25:00,673 --> 01:25:01,673
Whatever you decide,

1460
01:25:05,047 --> 01:25:06,586
I cannot walk away
from Kartu's life.

1461
01:25:09,721 --> 01:25:10,781
I mean, I refuse.

1462
01:25:12,699 --> 01:25:14,372
[Tense music]

1463
01:25:16,440 --> 01:25:17,911
[Tense music]

1464
01:25:19,166 --> 01:25:23,316
He is as much my son
as he is the two of yours.

1465
01:25:25,243 --> 01:25:27,318
[Tense music]

1466
01:25:27,599 --> 01:25:29,552
[Walks]

1467
01:25:29,710 --> 01:25:31,505
[Tense music]

1468
01:25:32,372 --> 01:25:33,905
[Opens door wide]

1469
01:25:36,130 --> 01:25:37,514
[Tense music]

1470
01:25:38,653 --> 01:25:40,054
[Tense music]

1471
01:25:41,692 --> 01:25:43,698
[Footsteps]

1472
01:25:44,889 --> 01:25:46,097
Hey, hi!

1473
01:25:46,554 --> 01:25:50,877
How cheap can you be! You know
how much it bothers me, don't you?

1474
01:25:50,878 --> 01:25:53,584
You know how much I can't stand it!
You know it! You know!

1475
01:25:53,585 --> 01:25:54,612
Hey, control yourself!

1476
01:25:55,584 --> 01:25:57,797
You! Don't interfere! This
has nothing to do with you!

1477
01:25:57,798 --> 01:26:02,544
Wasn't I clear enough? What part did you not understand?
- Hey! Hey, stop!

1478
01:26:02,545 --> 01:26:06,008
I told you clearly!
Don't you understand?

1479
01:26:06,559 --> 01:26:10,514
Shut up! Let me go. Leave me be!

1480
01:26:10,609 --> 01:26:13,716
Don't you get it? Don't you get it?

1481
01:26:14,005 --> 01:26:16,081
[Clangs]

1482
01:26:17,167 --> 01:26:18,770
[Breathing heavily]

1483
01:26:19,970 --> 01:26:22,107
[Sighs]

1484
01:26:23,710 --> 01:26:25,707
[Sighs]

1485
01:26:34,037 --> 01:26:36,542
Sorry.
- Sorry.

1486
01:26:37,208 --> 01:26:38,208
[Sighs]

1487
01:26:38,627 --> 01:26:39,627
[Birds chirping]

1488
01:26:47,301 --> 01:26:52,238
Is it such a problem for
you to see my side of things?

1489
01:26:58,505 --> 01:27:02,425
And then you have the audacity to tell my Dad to
not tell me about the money you borrowed from him.

1490
01:27:03,248 --> 01:27:05,648
He didn't listen to me, did he?
- Mom told me.

1491
01:27:11,228 --> 01:27:12,761
Did you try to see
my side of things?

1492
01:27:14,988 --> 01:27:16,668
Did you even notice
me working my ass off?

1493
01:27:21,809 --> 01:27:26,127
It's so humiliating to constantly
have to take on substandard work.

1494
01:27:26,854 --> 01:27:28,361
[Birds chirping]

1495
01:27:29,368 --> 01:27:31,260
[Awkward silent]

1496
01:27:31,926 --> 01:27:34,965
Do you even understand
the concept of money?

1497
01:27:35,405 --> 01:27:36,841
[Birds chirping]

1498
01:27:37,375 --> 01:27:39,153
[Birds chirping]

1499
01:27:42,114 --> 01:27:45,626
People spend their whole lives trying to make money and still?
- Oh, shut your trap!

1500
01:27:45,942 --> 01:27:47,396
[Birds chirping]

1501
01:27:49,183 --> 01:27:50,724
[Birds chirping]

1502
01:27:52,800 --> 01:27:53,800
Enough.

1503
01:27:54,202 --> 01:27:55,840
[Tense moment]

1504
01:27:57,188 --> 01:27:58,908
Let's put an end to
this. It's not working.

1505
01:27:59,361 --> 01:28:01,156
[Tense music]

1506
01:28:03,294 --> 01:28:04,914
[Sobs]

1507
01:28:06,534 --> 01:28:08,514
[Birds chirping]

1508
01:28:11,089 --> 01:28:12,937
[Sighs]

1509
01:28:16,064 --> 01:28:18,026
[Tense music]

1510
01:28:20,829 --> 01:28:23,440
[Tense music]

1511
01:28:25,752 --> 01:28:27,083
[Tense music]

1512
01:28:27,734 --> 01:28:28,739
Okay. Let's stop.

1513
01:28:32,196 --> 01:28:34,894
[Tense music]

1514
01:28:46,824 --> 01:28:49,206
What do you do when you get angry?

1515
01:28:50,301 --> 01:28:51,387
I never get angry.

1516
01:28:51,773 --> 01:28:52,316
[Footsteps]

1517
01:28:52,552 --> 01:28:53,552
Shut up.

1518
01:28:53,998 --> 01:28:54,998
[Chuckles]

1519
01:28:55,303 --> 01:28:56,398
I don't. Really.

1520
01:28:56,739 --> 01:29:00,471
Nothing makes you angry?
- Nope. Ask anyone.

1521
01:29:01,741 --> 01:29:06,336
Ever since I was a baby, I just don't get angry.
- Liar!

1522
01:29:06,337 --> 01:29:07,337
Hey!

1523
01:29:07,425 --> 01:29:08,817
[Birds chirping]

1524
01:29:08,818 --> 01:29:10,418
Go ahead. Try to make
me lose my temper.

1525
01:29:11,919 --> 01:29:13,592
[Footsteps]

1526
01:29:19,846 --> 01:29:22,406
To tell you the truth, whenever
I get angry, I feel like crying.

1527
01:29:23,113 --> 01:29:24,549
[Birds chirping]

1528
01:29:25,214 --> 01:29:27,887
Even I cry sometimes.
- Really?

1529
01:29:28,447 --> 01:29:29,595
[Indistinct chatter]

1530
01:29:30,164 --> 01:29:32,976
To tell you the truth, I
cry at the drop of a hat.

1531
01:29:34,281 --> 01:29:37,311
I cry a lot. Ma
says crying is good.

1532
01:29:37,820 --> 01:29:39,431
[Footsteps]

1533
01:29:44,021 --> 01:29:45,230
Your Ma is right.

1534
01:29:45,729 --> 01:29:46,973
[Birds chirping]

1535
01:29:47,288 --> 01:29:49,749
What was Ma like back
when you were friends?

1536
01:29:50,231 --> 01:29:51,317
[Tense music]

1537
01:29:52,815 --> 01:29:53,815
She was hardworking.

1538
01:29:54,934 --> 01:29:56,305
And very funny.

1539
01:29:56,502 --> 01:29:58,550
[Chuckles]

1540
01:29:59,007 --> 01:30:00,330
And she was a chatterbox.

1541
01:30:01,547 --> 01:30:07,644
When she doesn't have answers, she uses her hands a lot.
- Does she? How?

1542
01:30:08,406 --> 01:30:09,406
Like this.

1543
01:30:11,287 --> 01:30:13,127
Like this?
- Yes.

1544
01:30:13,416 --> 01:30:15,754
Did she do that back then too?

1545
01:30:16,639 --> 01:30:19,512
Maybe. I didn't notice.

1546
01:30:20,055 --> 01:30:21,860
[Train chugging]

1547
01:30:22,000 --> 01:30:24,522
[Train speeding]

1548
01:30:24,733 --> 01:30:25,994
[Bell]

1549
01:30:26,547 --> 01:30:29,787
How soon can I be discharged?

1550
01:30:30,297 --> 01:30:34,175
Well, for now just take it
slow and get lots of rest.

1551
01:30:34,422 --> 01:30:37,924
My wife is alone at
home, that's why?

1552
01:30:38,214 --> 01:30:44,651
If you stay calm and get your rest properly,
we could let you go by tomorrow afternoon.

1553
01:30:45,080 --> 01:30:47,550
Please behave yourself!

1554
01:30:48,181 --> 01:30:53,068
Luckily it was not a
fracture, it is a contusion.

1555
01:30:53,480 --> 01:30:55,022
Ah that's a relief!

1556
01:30:55,922 --> 01:30:57,282
He is a mischievous boy, this one.

1557
01:30:57,755 --> 01:30:58,755
Now be a good boy!

1558
01:30:58,963 --> 01:31:00,733
Be a good boy!

1559
01:31:03,588 --> 01:31:05,611
[Machine whirring]

1560
01:31:06,855 --> 01:31:07,855
Kartikeya?

1561
01:31:07,968 --> 01:31:09,448
[Machine whirring]

1562
01:31:09,868 --> 01:31:10,868
What's going on?

1563
01:31:11,555 --> 01:31:12,635
Are you trying to trick me?

1564
01:31:13,810 --> 01:31:14,810
Listen?

1565
01:31:15,763 --> 01:31:18,733
Is it okay if I don't
brush tonight?

1566
01:31:20,879 --> 01:31:21,956
[Exhales]

1567
01:31:22,680 --> 01:31:23,680
Okay.

1568
01:31:23,871 --> 01:31:24,978
But you won't tell her.

1569
01:31:25,414 --> 01:31:27,273
You don't tell her either.

1570
01:31:32,213 --> 01:31:33,264
[Phone vibrating]

1571
01:31:34,184 --> 01:31:35,226
[Phone vibrating]

1572
01:31:37,679 --> 01:31:38,195
Hi.

1573
01:31:38,677 --> 01:31:40,455
[Folding clothes]

1574
01:31:43,337 --> 01:31:44,337
Everything is fine.

1575
01:31:45,264 --> 01:31:47,464
I locked up at the shop and
handed the key to Nori-san.

1576
01:31:47,797 --> 01:31:51,071
We had dinner on the way
home. And Kartu is fast asleep.

1577
01:31:52,411 --> 01:31:53,411
[Soft chuckle]

1578
01:31:53,962 --> 01:31:56,738
Have you put your phone for charging?
- Yes.

1579
01:31:59,480 --> 01:32:00,480
Umm-mm.

1580
01:32:02,995 --> 01:32:05,635
I don't know how I would have
managed today if it weren't for you.

1581
01:32:06,041 --> 01:32:07,041
It's not such a big deal.

1582
01:32:07,964 --> 01:32:08,964
Give me a minute, please?

1583
01:32:10,380 --> 01:32:12,922
I've made milkshake.
- Milkshake?

1584
01:32:12,923 --> 01:32:13,923
[Whisper]

1585
01:32:15,697 --> 01:32:17,177
[Footsteps]

1586
01:32:18,456 --> 01:32:19,927
[Clang]

1587
01:32:20,639 --> 01:32:22,047
Kartu makes for the best company.

1588
01:32:23,694 --> 01:32:24,894
We've been getting along well.

1589
01:32:25,472 --> 01:32:28,450
Really?
- Yes, really.

1590
01:32:31,306 --> 01:32:32,306
[Cradles the phone]

1591
01:32:32,684 --> 01:32:33,684
[Cradles the phone]

1592
01:32:39,455 --> 01:32:40,611
[Paper ruffling]

1593
01:32:41,601 --> 01:32:44,185
[Tense music]

1594
01:32:45,280 --> 01:32:47,066
Are you going to tell him?

1595
01:32:49,389 --> 01:32:50,912
He needs to know.

1596
01:32:51,490 --> 01:32:53,391
[Tense music]

1597
01:32:54,512 --> 01:32:56,115
[Tense music]

1598
01:32:57,682 --> 01:33:03,475
I remember when Kartu

1599
01:33:03,709 --> 01:33:07,869
and I
went for our first walk together.

1600
01:33:08,815 --> 01:33:09,534
[Chuckles]

1601
01:33:09,755 --> 01:33:13,060
That tiny little
palm gripping mine.

1602
01:33:13,061 --> 01:33:14,185
[Sighs]

1603
01:33:14,680 --> 01:33:18,372
My heart melted.

1604
01:33:19,589 --> 01:33:23,241
That's when I thought

1605
01:33:23,242 --> 01:33:26,614
for the first time, I might be
able to love unconditionally.

1606
01:33:27,446 --> 01:33:32,877
Kartu gave me this car because I'm in the hospital.
He said, “Haru-san, you shouldn't feel alone.”

1607
01:33:33,209 --> 01:33:34,331
[Chuckles]

1608
01:33:35,172 --> 01:33:36,345
[Hands shivering]

1609
01:33:36,897 --> 01:33:41,154
You can see he
loves the boy already.

1610
01:33:41,977 --> 01:33:45,656
If it is so obvious,
why can't he see it?

1611
01:33:46,488 --> 01:33:48,231
May be he is scared.

1612
01:33:49,607 --> 01:33:50,721
[Breathes in]

1613
01:33:50,722 --> 01:33:56,342
Some people don't see
things on their own.

1614
01:33:58,217 --> 01:34:00,862
They've to be shown.

1615
01:34:04,068 --> 01:34:05,068
Umm.

1616
01:34:09,209 --> 01:34:10,786
[Tense music]

1617
01:34:12,582 --> 01:34:14,728
[Tense music]

1618
01:34:19,285 --> 01:34:20,285
Kartikeya?

1619
01:34:20,991 --> 01:34:22,050
It's very late now.

1620
01:34:23,548 --> 01:34:27,131
I'm switching off the lights.
You need to sleep now. Okay?

1621
01:34:27,507 --> 01:34:28,918
[Tense music]

1622
01:34:29,408 --> 01:34:31,326
[Footsteps]

1623
01:34:31,974 --> 01:34:32,974
[Switch off lights]

1624
01:34:33,612 --> 01:34:34,612
Come here.

1625
01:34:34,996 --> 01:34:37,309
[Footsteps]

1626
01:34:38,223 --> 01:34:39,223
What is it?

1627
01:34:40,991 --> 01:34:42,523
Listen?
- Hmmm.

1628
01:34:43,496 --> 01:34:46,045
It would be okay if you
called me Kartu now.

1629
01:34:50,170 --> 01:34:51,170
[Sighs]

1630
01:34:53,280 --> 01:34:54,280
[Sighs]

1631
01:34:54,532 --> 01:34:55,653
[Sighs]

1632
01:34:56,494 --> 01:34:58,246
[Sighs]

1633
01:34:59,297 --> 01:35:00,935
[Tense music]

1634
01:35:02,521 --> 01:35:04,509
[Tense music]

1635
01:35:05,648 --> 01:35:07,215
[Tense music]

1636
01:35:07,767 --> 01:35:10,544
[Sobs]

1637
01:35:10,850 --> 01:35:12,890
[Sobs]

1638
01:35:12,891 --> 01:35:17,674
[Sighs]

1639
01:35:17,866 --> 01:35:20,599
[Tense music]

1640
01:35:20,810 --> 01:35:22,991
[Tense music]

1641
01:35:23,586 --> 01:35:25,641
[Tense music]

1642
01:35:25,642 --> 01:35:28,071
[Grins]

1643
01:35:28,202 --> 01:35:30,830
[Hugs]

1644
01:35:31,767 --> 01:35:33,799
[Kissing]

1645
01:35:35,210 --> 01:35:36,383
Five minutes. I Promise.

1646
01:35:36,805 --> 01:35:37,930
Okay.
- Okay.

1647
01:35:40,728 --> 01:35:41,779
[Footsteps]

1648
01:35:44,337 --> 01:35:45,721
[Punching keyboard]

1649
01:35:46,728 --> 01:35:49,513
[Jumps]

1650
01:35:50,205 --> 01:35:54,926
Chef special Chicken Afghani and Baigun Bhaja
will be ready in an hour. Just one hour.

1651
01:35:56,249 --> 01:35:57,878
Have you diced the onion?
- Yes.

1652
01:35:58,364 --> 01:35:59,364
Where is it?

1653
01:36:00,453 --> 01:36:01,453
Inside.

1654
01:36:02,485 --> 01:36:03,485
Inside where?

1655
01:36:05,131 --> 01:36:07,294
On the kitchen counter.
- Where on the kitchen counter?

1656
01:36:09,081 --> 01:36:10,947
It's right there. Just look.
- Okay!

1657
01:36:12,614 --> 01:36:13,814
I'll just have a quick shower.

1658
01:36:15,659 --> 01:36:18,226
No, no. Just cancel it then.

1659
01:36:18,769 --> 01:36:21,458
Yes, cancel it and
refund the money.

1660
01:36:22,455 --> 01:36:23,455
Yes, okay.

1661
01:36:28,018 --> 01:36:29,945
Who was that?
- Leave it.

1662
01:36:31,093 --> 01:36:32,093
Come on.

1663
01:36:32,766 --> 01:36:34,006
What did you want a refund for?

1664
01:36:36,462 --> 01:36:37,462
For the cake.

1665
01:36:39,843 --> 01:36:41,560
Our cake?
- Hmm.

1666
01:36:42,156 --> 01:36:43,645
Sorry?
- Yes.

1667
01:36:44,164 --> 01:36:46,912
Why?
- They didn't have a baked one.

1668
01:36:47,586 --> 01:36:48,586
Come on.

1669
01:36:51,948 --> 01:36:55,388
I pre-ordered it day before yesterday. Why
do they accept orders if they can't deliver?

1670
01:36:55,830 --> 01:36:56,830
Look here. Which one?

1671
01:36:58,255 --> 01:37:00,406
So, which one have you ordered now?
- No cake.

1672
01:37:01,176 --> 01:37:02,176
[Clicks]

1673
01:37:05,430 --> 01:37:06,430
What do you mean no cake?

1674
01:37:09,340 --> 01:37:11,020
I mean I haven't
ordered any cake instead.

1675
01:37:12,493 --> 01:37:14,210
[Bends]

1676
01:37:14,613 --> 01:37:16,408
So, there's no cake coming?
- No.

1677
01:37:17,241 --> 01:37:19,045
[Nods head]

1678
01:37:19,889 --> 01:37:21,249
So, what are we going to cut then?

1679
01:37:21,857 --> 01:37:22,596
[Chuckles]

1680
01:37:22,597 --> 01:37:23,597
We can cut the chicken.

1681
01:37:24,992 --> 01:37:27,016
I hate those disgusting
gelatin cakes.

1682
01:37:28,846 --> 01:37:30,607
[Pulls]

1683
01:37:31,807 --> 01:37:33,068
[Downtrodden]

1684
01:37:33,222 --> 01:37:36,589
You could have checked with me once.
- It's fine. Just let it go.

1685
01:37:37,380 --> 01:37:38,900
I wouldn't have
minded a gelatin cake.

1686
01:37:40,264 --> 01:37:43,384
You don't even eat cake. I don't know why you're whining.
- I wanted one today.

1687
01:37:45,347 --> 01:37:47,976
Today may not be important
to you, but I'm excited about it.

1688
01:37:49,255 --> 01:37:51,252
Oh, please. What is this mood?

1689
01:37:51,603 --> 01:37:54,660
'My cake'. 'I like
it'. 'I don't want it'.

1690
01:37:55,404 --> 01:37:56,404
So selfish.

1691
01:37:57,541 --> 01:37:59,929
You don't give a rat's ass about the other person.
- No, I don't.

1692
01:37:59,930 --> 01:38:04,338
Exactly. You don't. The
other person doesn't matter.

1693
01:38:05,547 --> 01:38:09,270
It doesn't concern you.
You don't even notice.

1694
01:38:10,636 --> 01:38:16,312
You don't want to listen to the other person at
all. Everything has to centre around I, me, myself.

1695
01:38:17,264 --> 01:38:19,982
Who cares about anyone
else? They're empty-headed.

1696
01:38:21,805 --> 01:38:23,045
They're too dumb to care about.

1697
01:38:23,363 --> 01:38:26,714
And what about you? “I'm such
a victim”. “No one listens to me.”

1698
01:38:26,715 --> 01:38:31,330
“Nothing ever works out for me.” “My Dad is
this; my Dad is that.” “My Mom is this...”

1699
01:38:31,331 --> 01:38:33,436
But you still want to
drive your Dad's car!

1700
01:38:34,242 --> 01:38:35,242
[Clangs]

1701
01:38:36,073 --> 01:38:37,793
What had I asked you
to do with the onions?

1702
01:38:40,058 --> 01:38:41,058
What?

1703
01:38:41,468 --> 01:38:42,572
[Shakes pan]

1704
01:38:43,255 --> 01:38:44,255
The onion.

1705
01:38:45,979 --> 01:38:48,992
When I said I'd cook chicken, what
had I asked you to do with the onions?

1706
01:38:49,868 --> 01:38:51,508
What did you ask for?
You said dice them.

1707
01:38:51,903 --> 01:38:54,677
Did I ask you to
slice it or chop it?

1708
01:38:55,141 --> 01:38:56,452
[Tense moment]

1709
01:38:56,453 --> 01:38:57,874
Oh, did you specify?

1710
01:38:58,181 --> 01:38:59,181
[Sizzling]

1711
01:38:59,339 --> 01:39:01,921
I had clearly asked
you to slice the onions.

1712
01:39:02,604 --> 01:39:04,514
[Sizzling]

1713
01:39:04,864 --> 01:39:09,235
Okay, maybe you did.
- Not, not maybe. I had asked you to slice the onions.

1714
01:39:09,414 --> 01:39:10,414
Okay, fine.

1715
01:39:10,829 --> 01:39:11,889
[Sizzling]

1716
01:39:12,255 --> 01:39:13,375
Why didn't you listen to me?

1717
01:39:13,562 --> 01:39:14,706
[Sizzling]

1718
01:39:14,707 --> 01:39:16,796
What have I done then?
- Look at what you have done.

1719
01:39:16,797 --> 01:39:19,711
You have chopped it.
You have chopped it.

1720
01:39:19,956 --> 01:39:23,346
How does it matter? It
was whole and now it isn't.

1721
01:39:26,061 --> 01:39:27,061
[Clang]

1722
01:39:28,255 --> 01:39:29,255
Seriously?

1723
01:39:31,722 --> 01:39:34,041
You have no respect for me.
- What did you say?

1724
01:39:34,899 --> 01:39:41,381
If you want me to hear, you're going to have to speak louder.
- You do not respect me!

1725
01:39:41,714 --> 01:39:42,765
[Bangs the ball]

1726
01:39:43,606 --> 01:39:47,135
Why? Because I didn't cut the onion the way you wanted?
- Yes.

1727
01:39:48,449 --> 01:39:50,201
Yes.

1728
01:39:50,998 --> 01:39:51,998
[Bangs the ball]

1729
01:39:52,803 --> 01:39:57,235
Okay. Next time, I'll make sure it is chopped.
- Not chopped, sliced!

1730
01:39:59,521 --> 01:40:01,457
[Splash]

1731
01:40:05,182 --> 01:40:06,575
[Footsteps]

1732
01:40:08,948 --> 01:40:10,262
[Patting]

1733
01:40:11,097 --> 01:40:12,741
Okay, sliced.

1734
01:40:13,486 --> 01:40:15,570
[Hugs]

1735
01:40:20,922 --> 01:40:22,122
[Insect creaking]

1736
01:40:23,015 --> 01:40:24,189
Happy second anniversary.

1737
01:40:24,794 --> 01:40:26,791
[Insect creaking]

1738
01:40:27,537 --> 01:40:28,684
[Sniffs]

1739
01:40:31,764 --> 01:40:35,008
Let's not talk about
onions anymore.

1740
01:40:35,464 --> 01:40:37,417
[Insect creaking]

1741
01:40:38,249 --> 01:40:39,659
[Animal calls]

1742
01:40:40,005 --> 01:40:43,154
Systematic desensitization.

1743
01:40:43,566 --> 01:40:45,248
[Insect creaking]

1744
01:40:45,966 --> 01:40:46,966
What?

1745
01:40:47,272 --> 01:40:49,426
[Insect creaking]

1746
01:40:50,915 --> 01:40:56,328
This? this thing that you do to me.

1747
01:40:56,635 --> 01:40:58,133
[Insect creaking]

1748
01:40:58,527 --> 01:41:00,944
It is systematic desensitization.

1749
01:41:00,945 --> 01:41:05,166
Don't throw nonsensical
jargon from Instagram at me.

1750
01:41:05,534 --> 01:41:07,820
Ignore anything the other
person ever says or asks for.

1751
01:41:11,197 --> 01:41:16,326
Until they start to
believe they're unworthy.

1752
01:41:17,902 --> 01:41:20,547
That they don't deserve
to be treated well.

1753
01:41:21,005 --> 01:41:22,725
If that's the case, why
don't you leave me.

1754
01:41:23,508 --> 01:41:29,061
Get up, come on. Leave me and go. We're not
bound to each other. Come on, get up. Leave.

1755
01:41:29,289 --> 01:41:32,057
Go, get going now.
Go!

1756
01:41:35,963 --> 01:41:39,064
As depressing as it is to be with you,
it is more depressing to be alone.

1757
01:41:41,239 --> 01:41:44,836
Whose problem is that?
- It's mine!

1758
01:41:45,204 --> 01:41:47,158
[Dog barking]

1759
01:41:48,612 --> 01:41:50,959
[Insect creaking]

1760
01:41:52,330 --> 01:41:57,003
It is my problem. So
then? Yes, it is my problem.

1761
01:41:57,791 --> 01:42:00,069
[Insect creaking]

1762
01:42:00,708 --> 01:42:02,582
[Dog barks]

1763
01:42:02,907 --> 01:42:04,299
Why should I respect you?

1764
01:42:05,105 --> 01:42:06,909
[Insect creaking]

1765
01:42:08,845 --> 01:42:11,263
[Dog barks]

1766
01:42:12,077 --> 01:42:13,715
[Insect creaking]

1767
01:42:14,055 --> 01:42:15,651
'Why'?
- Yes. Why?

1768
01:42:15,993 --> 01:42:17,666
[Dog barks]

1769
01:42:18,289 --> 01:42:20,153
What about you is
worth taking seriously?

1770
01:42:20,521 --> 01:42:22,019
[Insect creaking]

1771
01:42:23,788 --> 01:42:26,188
[Insect creaking]

1772
01:42:27,721 --> 01:42:29,289
Is there nothing?
- What is?

1773
01:42:29,692 --> 01:42:31,321
[Sobs]

1774
01:42:32,109 --> 01:42:33,555
[Sniffs]

1775
01:42:34,622 --> 01:42:37,225
Do you not get anything from me?
- What do I get?

1776
01:42:37,777 --> 01:42:39,450
[Sobs]

1777
01:42:40,212 --> 01:42:41,903
How much more will you take?

1778
01:42:42,210 --> 01:42:43,533
[Sobs]

1779
01:42:45,039 --> 01:42:46,520
[Sniffs]

1780
01:42:47,369 --> 01:42:49,174
How much more?

1781
01:42:49,699 --> 01:42:51,320
[Sits]

1782
01:42:51,460 --> 01:42:52,607
I feel empty.

1783
01:42:52,968 --> 01:42:54,194
[Sobs]

1784
01:42:54,755 --> 01:42:55,902
[Sniffs]

1785
01:42:56,034 --> 01:42:57,034
[Sniffs]

1786
01:42:57,295 --> 01:42:59,450
I can only give if
I'm left with anything.

1787
01:42:59,931 --> 01:43:01,972
[Insect creaking]

1788
01:43:03,934 --> 01:43:05,362
[Clangs]

1789
01:43:08,682 --> 01:43:09,882
Don't be in a hurry.

1790
01:43:10,355 --> 01:43:11,376
[Sniffs]

1791
01:43:11,377 --> 01:43:12,937
Think about it
carefully and seriously.

1792
01:43:13,867 --> 01:43:14,867
[Sniffs]

1793
01:43:15,269 --> 01:43:16,688
What do I get from you?

1794
01:43:17,178 --> 01:43:19,280
[Sniffs]

1795
01:43:19,850 --> 01:43:21,125
[Insect creaking]

1796
01:43:21,126 --> 01:43:24,115
You're constantly cursing your Dad.
He gave me money, at least.

1797
01:43:24,475 --> 01:43:25,767
[Insect creaking]

1798
01:43:25,768 --> 01:43:27,882
He asked about my well being.

1799
01:43:28,547 --> 01:43:31,987
When have you ever supported me with anything?
- Do the two of you talk behind my back?

1800
01:43:34,380 --> 01:43:37,315
He asked me if the pressure
from the loan is any less.

1801
01:43:37,710 --> 01:43:39,094
[Sobs]

1802
01:43:39,733 --> 01:43:40,813
Did it occur to you to ask?

1803
01:43:41,914 --> 01:43:42,914
[Sniffs]

1804
01:43:43,902 --> 01:43:45,383
[Insect creaking]

1805
01:43:46,828 --> 01:43:47,914
[Sniffs]

1806
01:43:49,502 --> 01:43:50,734
Return the money you borrowed.

1807
01:43:52,670 --> 01:43:54,185
[Tense silent]

1808
01:43:55,039 --> 01:43:56,402
How does it concern you?

1809
01:43:57,426 --> 01:43:58,985
[Insect creaking]

1810
01:44:07,305 --> 01:44:08,305
Where's your phone?

1811
01:44:08,734 --> 01:44:10,075
[Clangs]

1812
01:44:10,497 --> 01:44:13,797
What?
- Transfer the money to me right now.

1813
01:44:14,358 --> 01:44:15,715
[Clangs]

1814
01:44:16,083 --> 01:44:17,336
What are you doing?

1815
01:44:17,660 --> 01:44:19,280
[Clangs]

1816
01:44:19,639 --> 01:44:21,409
Return the money.
- My phone isn't in there.

1817
01:44:21,952 --> 01:44:22,816
[Clutters]

1818
01:44:22,817 --> 01:44:24,212
What did you do with the money?

1819
01:44:24,964 --> 01:44:28,180
What do you mean? I returned it to
the people I had borrowed money from.

1820
01:44:29,755 --> 01:44:31,622
All of it?
- Most of it.

1821
01:44:32,086 --> 01:44:35,310
And the rest?
- It's in the bank.

1822
01:44:36,964 --> 01:44:38,515
Where is your phone?

1823
01:44:39,339 --> 01:44:40,539
[Clanging]

1824
01:44:40,889 --> 01:44:41,889
[Insect creaking]

1825
01:44:42,014 --> 01:44:44,775
Where is it? Where have you kept your phone?
- I won't give it to you!

1826
01:44:46,156 --> 01:44:50,559
Return the money. Return it.
- I do plan to return it. But to your Dad.

1827
01:44:50,791 --> 01:44:51,921
What is my Dad to you even?

1828
01:44:52,430 --> 01:44:54,847
If we're not going to be together,
what is my Dad to you?

1829
01:44:54,972 --> 01:44:58,492
Oh, I see. So now we're not going to be together, are we?
- Just return the bloody money!

1830
01:45:00,470 --> 01:45:02,397
[Sobs]

1831
01:45:06,619 --> 01:45:08,695
[Sobs]

1832
01:45:10,164 --> 01:45:11,506
I won't return it.

1833
01:45:12,443 --> 01:45:16,622
Not today, not tomorrow, not ever.
Let's see what you do.

1834
01:45:17,016 --> 01:45:18,295
[Sobs]

1835
01:45:22,017 --> 01:45:23,017
[Sobs]

1836
01:45:23,716 --> 01:45:24,716
[Sobs]

1837
01:45:26,099 --> 01:45:27,299
[Cracking]

1838
01:45:30,764 --> 01:45:31,764
Give me your phone.

1839
01:45:33,325 --> 01:45:34,333
[Tense music]

1840
01:45:35,033 --> 01:45:36,033
Give me your phone.

1841
01:45:37,311 --> 01:45:38,813
Give me your phone.
- Let me go.

1842
01:45:38,814 --> 01:45:40,054
Give me the phone.
- No, I won't.

1843
01:45:40,055 --> 01:45:42,452
Give it to me.
- No!

1844
01:45:42,908 --> 01:45:46,350
Give me the phone. Give it.
Give the phone.

1845
01:45:50,318 --> 01:45:52,770
What is the password?
- Not going to tell you.

1846
01:45:53,681 --> 01:45:56,537
What's the password? Tell me the password.
- No. Never.

1847
01:45:57,555 --> 01:45:59,796
Give me the password.
- I am not going to. Don't you get it?

1848
01:45:59,797 --> 01:46:01,460
Tell me the password.
- No!

1849
01:46:03,185 --> 01:46:03,903
[Clanging]

1850
01:46:04,139 --> 01:46:06,889
Tell me the password. Tell me the password now.
- Put down my laptop.

1851
01:46:06,890 --> 01:46:08,890
Tell me the password.
- Put down my laptop, please.

1852
01:46:09,299 --> 01:46:10,832
Password.
- Please put down the laptop.

1853
01:46:11,410 --> 01:46:13,013
Tell me the password.
- Put down my laptop first.

1854
01:46:13,014 --> 01:46:14,878
Tell me the password!
- Put down my laptop.

1855
01:46:15,211 --> 01:46:16,473
Password.
- Put the laptop down!

1856
01:46:16,630 --> 01:46:20,607
Give me the password. One last time.
- Put down my laptop!

1857
01:46:20,887 --> 01:46:22,744
Leave it. It's my earning.

1858
01:46:23,016 --> 01:46:24,978
Just give me the password.

1859
